When editing post functions on a transition within a workflow a new tab is opened which leads to a duplicate tab. Once you have published your post function edit/addition in this new tab, you are returned to 'view workflow' instead of edit.

This leads to an old tab, in 'edit' mode which is now redundant as the workflow has been updated, and a newer tab which is in view mode, which you then have to put back into edit mode to make further changes.

This should all be done within one tab as it means closing old tabs, and then having to put the new tabs back into edit mode to make changes. Once you have published your post function change, you should be returned back to the screen you were viewing when you clicked on 'post functions'.

